The paper deals with algorithmic self-assembly, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The paper also discusses the computational power of this model, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY). The paper uses geometric concepts to analyze the growth process, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and distributed algorithms (cs.DS).
